6. Full page-level functional rendering

f49v can be rendered as an internal instruction page:

This regime is read through closed process chains.

A process may begin in preparation or procedure-initiation, enter a field, move toward output, and close.

An active process may enter a field, stabilize, regulate, initiate a procedure, return to field, move to output, and close.

A graded process may enter a field, become regulated, initiate procedure, return to field, move to output, and close.

An active field may be transformed and closed.

An active frame may be stabilized and closed.

More compactly:

prepare/initiate -> field -> output -> close
activate -> field -> stabilize -> regulate -> operate -> field -> output -> close
grade -> field -> regulate -> operate -> field -> output -> close
activate -> field -> transform -> close
activate -> stabilize -> close
